description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Purpose: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of the Stop Smoking Practitioner is to support the delivery of evidenced based, equitable stop smoking services to help to reduce the inequalities throughout County Durham. This will include the delivery of services within areas of most deprivation. It is essential that the postholder can work flexibly, independently and as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will work under the line management of the Community Specialist Service Lead and supervised by the Head of Smoking Cessation. The role will be varied, challenging, and rewarding as the services develop as part of the national 10 - year plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a motivated, passionate, organised, and proactive individual with significant experience in smoking cessation and working within a community environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of the essential requirements are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant degree (health/social care/public health)/ professional qualification / or significant experience working within smoking cessation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working in a community setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NCSCT Practitioner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more details, please see attached job description.&lt;/p&gt;
